metadata.name: Disdain #10
metadata.description:
Disdain — "The feeling that someone or something is unworthy of one's consideration or respect"

This is a project created for the #Genuary32nd minting party. 
Based on my entry for #Genuary26, the prompt was "My Kid Could Have Done That". 
It’s also my first project published on fxhash!

The idea behind it was to replicate drawings made by my kids but give it some refined composition and colour selection so that it could pass as a "real" artist’s piece.

-----

Press "s" key to save it as a PNG image.

To get the highest resolution, open in live view, zoom out totally and refresh the page before hitting "s" to save the image.

-----

Made with p5.js by João Pescada - February 2023.

metadata.name: Candles #9
metadata.description:
Why are you into NFT's? Chasing the profit or loving the art? The "Candles" project arises from this dilemma.

Once you mint, the market will open and randomly decide whether you win or lose. 
There is Dark and Light Mode and very rarely you will mint a Single Loop Trader Mode piece, which is by far the dullest version, and at the same time the rarest and so the most valuable... 
So question yourself, would I rather mint a dull and valuable piece, or a colorful piece of art to enjoy.

And oh, If you press "r" you will be able to see your profit (or loss) and toggle it on/off. just for fun :-)

@Elum0x, pure Javascript, Brussels 2022.

metadata.name: Annihilate This Week #206
metadata.description:
This is a companion piece to "Saturday Night's Alright (For Fighting)" (project #14045). Same algorithm of the previous one, only slightly modified, the main difference is that here the daily variations are all mixed up together and the output doesn't change based on the current day.

This is intended to be a gift for all collectors and the community of fx(hash) that showed so much support for the "Saturday" project, really beyond my expectations.

50% of the royalties goes to the minter, do with the piece whatever you'd like, hold it, sell or trade it, or even burn it if you really don't like it :)

Thank you!

----

Made with p5.js

metadata.name: Mount Doodle #233
metadata.description:
Tried my best to make every doodle aesthetically pleasing to the eyes.
However, just like nature, beauty often lies in imperfections. :)

Made with p5.js.
Primary split 5% with The Processing Foundation.

Keys
- 1: view 1000px png (Default)
- 2: download 2000px png
- 4: download 4000px png
- 8: download 8000px png
- s: save the image as PNG

When downloading higher resolution pngs, it might take several seconds to redraw the whole image. Download will start immediately after redrawing is completed. Please bear with the slow rendering.

metadata.name: Tilemoji #220
metadata.description:
This collection of low resolution generative art is presented using emojis rather than an image, so it can be copied like normal text. You are also welcome to take a screenshot for sharing or printing. Most results are designed to fit in a 280 character tweet, except for rare extra large variants. There are five different generative algorithms possible, each with their own set of parameters. Emojis are rendered using the Twemoji font and may look different in some environments.

Thank you for supporting my work during the first year of fxhash. For me it has been a life changing experience. I am forever grateful for all of the art and friendships we've created. Many of us have met on social media, so I developed this special project with a fun way to display and share. Congrats to artists, collectors, and developers for an amazing year!

This work is part of the fxhash anniversary event (#fxhashturnsone)
All of primary sale proceeds will go to Save Pakistan

Code and Outputs are Copyright 2022 Frank Force
Artwork is released under CC BY-NC 4.0 (https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0)
Twemoji Graphics licensed under CC-BY 4.0 (https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0)

metadata.name: Wanderer #5
metadata.description:
Wanderer is an algorithm which uses hexagonal Truchet tiles to produce meandering paths of color. Originally created back in February, I am releasing it as part of this week's #fxhashturnsone celebration.

100% of primary sales will go the the Processing foundation.

Thank you to fx(hash) and to the entire generative art community. 

CONTROLS:

1-9: Increase resolution and save image in PNG format

For third party license information, please see license.md

David Brice Allen
November 2022
